    <text>
        <group>
            <text type="letter" xml:lang="fr" xml:id="letter-02633">
                <body>
                    <opener> 
                    <salute rend="inline">Sire!</salute></opener>
                    <p>Je sens trop parfaitement la part que Votre Majesté a au <rs type="event"
                            ref="events.xml#betro01">grand établissement</rs>, où je viens d'entrer,
                        pour oublier les remercîments que je Lui en dois, recevez les ici, Sire!</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>et persuadez Vous, que je ne le considérerai glorieux pour moi,
                            qu'alors que j'aurai eu l'occasion de Vous convaincre de ma
                            reconnaissance et de l'attachement, dont j'ai l'honneur d'être, Sire, de
                            Votre Majesté, la très humble et très obéissante Cousine et
                            Servante 
                        <persName ref="people.xml#cat01" type="signature" rend="below">Catherine.</persName></signed>
                        <dateline><placeName ref="places.xml#mos01">à Moscou</placeName>
                            <date when-custom="1744-07-21">ce 21 Juillet (1 d'Août)
                            1744</date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </body>
            </text>
            <text type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <body>
                    <opener>
                    <salute rend="inline">Sire!</salute></opener>
                    <p>I have too profound a sense of how much Your Majesty has contributed to the
                        great establishment into which I have just entered for me to be able to
                        forget the thanks which I owe you for it: receive them here, Sire!</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>and be persuaded that I shall not think it glorious for me, except
                            once I have had the chance to convince you of my gratitude and of the
                            affection with which I have the honour to be, Sire, Your Majesty's most
                            humble and most obedient Cousin and Servant
                        <persName rend="below">Catherine.</persName></signed>
                        <dateline>at Moscow this <date when-custom="1744-07-21">21 July (1 August) 1744</date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </body>
            </text>
        </group>
    </text>
